Package: bashic
Version: 1.0
Section: interpreters
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0)
Maintainer: BASHIC Project <andrew@turpin.co.za>
Description: BASIC interpreter written in bash
 BASHIC is a complete BASIC interpreter implemented entirely in bash.
 It supports classic DOS BASIC syntax including variables, control
 structures, arrays, and built-in functions. No external dependencies
 required beyond bash itself.
 .
 Features:
  - Classic DOS BASIC compatibility
  - Variables (numeric and string)
  - Control flow (IF/THEN, FOR/NEXT, WHILE/WEND, GOSUB/RETURN)
  - Built-in mathematical and string functions
  - Text-mode only (no graphics)
  - Line-numbered programs
Homepage: https://github.com/bank-builder/bashic
